args: The twelve Wyrmclan leaders are meeting to\ndiscuss the future of Hinomoto and the shogunate.
Yukimura had already begun packing to prepare\nfor the journey ahead, but...
Huh? Where'd my hand towel go?\nAnd where's my extra headband?
If you need assistance, Lady Yukimura,\ndo not hesitate to call on me.
As a Wyrmclan leader and as a military\ncommander, I've gotta do my own work!
Of course. If you change your mind,\nI will ever be here for you.
Okay, hand towel. Haaand toweeell...\nOh, there it is! Okay, great. Next...
One moment. Yukimura has yet to arrive.
*gasp* *wheeze* Sorry! Took longer than I\nthought to get ready—but I made it, yeah?
You are still late to an important meeting.\nThat's sloppy, Yuki. Very sloppy.
Leave the poor child be, Shingen.\nShe's only the slightest bit late.
Exactly! And now that everybody's here,\nlet's get this show on the road and\nfinish 'er up. Chop chop, people!
(Ugh. All this political talk is waaaay over\nmy head. Why can't we talk about fighting\nor something else I understand?)
(Oh, hey! I should review the half of that\nbook I DID read while I still remember it!)

(Lessee... The most important things to
remember when it comes to tactics are
your formations and...reconnaissance?
I think?)
Seimei has sent us his thoughts on the\nmatter in his absence. According to him...
(Oh yeah! I remember Seimei saying that\nonmyoji should use something for\nreconnaissance! What was it again...?)
What are your thoughts on the matter,\nYukimura?
Ha ha! You are quite the character\nindeed, Yukimura!
Thank goodness THAT'S over! I thought\nI was gonna fall asleep and have my\nbrain turn into oatmeal.
No, I was awake the entire time—\nI was just thinking about military tactics.
Wait, really? I don't remember you being\ninto that sorta thing.
I've just started to study up on it!\nI want to be able to command an army\njust like General Shingen.
But turns out I'm a lot better at\ncrackin' skulls than crackin' books.
If there's something you can't do,\njust pass it on to someone else!
What?! No! That's... I could never do that!
I'm gonna get better at being a Wyrmclan\nleader AND a commander, which means I\nhave to study until it sticks!
There is some truth to Mitsuhide's words.
It's admirable that you have the drive to\ntry to overcome your weaknesses.
Yeah, because of the burning spirit\nI inherited from you!
But that only applies to you as a warrior.
As a commander—as someone who must\noversee their vassals—that kind of thing\nwon't do at all.
That's right. Knowing when to count on\nothers to fill in for your own shortcomings\nis a vital skill for a commander.
Turning such matters over to another\nrequires a great amount of trust.
Do you have a trusting relationship\nbetween you and your vassals?
Well, I... I mean, ya know...
You have only just become a Wyrmclan\nleader, Yuki, and I do not expect you to\nunderstand all of these things instantly.
But if you truly wish to become a leader,\nyou must change your way of thinking.
So that's what a leader is...
Welcome home, Lady Yukimura. You must\nbe tired—permit me to unpack your bags.
No, it's fine. It's my luggage,\nso I should...
Oh, wait! I'm supposed to count on\nmy vassals and all that!
Er...yeaaaah. Actually, why don't you\nhandle the luggage?
GOOD GRAVY, WOMAN! You're incredible!\nThat bag's practically unpacking itself!
Hey, question: Where do you go to train in\nyour luggage martial arts or whatever?
It is not so impressive a thing, milady.\nI am simply used to it after serving nobles\nsuch as yourself for so long.
Ah, okay. So this is the result of your\ntraining in how to take care of people!
I suppose you could say that, milady.\n...And there. Your luggage is unpacked.
(That was way faster than if I had done it\nmyself. Look what counting on someone\nelse got me!)
(I think I'm finally starting to understand\nwhat the general was talking about...)
